1. Download and unzip BAM files with alignments from 
http://xfer.curie.fr/get/CkMVHqDo361/bam.zip 
and 
http://xfer.curie.fr/get/eGalAkbo3Lg/bam_constit.zip

2. Download and unzip GEM mappability files from http://xfer.curie.fr/get/7unymzXAl8X/gem_files.zip

3. Download and unzip .fa files with chromosome sequences from http://xfer.curie.fr/get/0dbKajSuTuZ/fa_files.zip

#COMMENT: SV-Bay only accepts files per chromosome. If you have one GEM and one BAM file for the whole genome, please use the following scripts to split them up:
#for GEM files:
python src/utils/sep_safe_gem.py yourBigGEMfile.gem outputDir/
python src/utils/separately_save_sam_chr.py yourBigBAMfile.gem outputDir/

What you can find in this folder:

simulated_reads_cnv.txt - output of Control-FREEC on the test data
centrom_hg19.txt - files with positions of centromere/telomere/unassabled regions to exclude
centrom_hg38.txt - files with positions of centromere/telomere/unassabled regions to exclude - to use for this example
config - a folder with two config files - for a constitutive (control) sample (config_germ.yaml) and a tumor sample (config.yaml)
